Military life bares almost no resemblance to military life. And that's why we miss it.

snippet.textDisplay:
You don't pull your cutaway and then start looking for your reserve handle - when you cut away, your harness will shift and you'll loose precious time. You either have one hand on each handle, or you grab the cutaway, fix your eyes on the reserve handle, then you pull cutaway. All training every on earth will teach you one of these two procedures.

And you should absolutely forget about the main potentially opening the reserve. It probably will, but your mindset should 100% be that you need to do the full procedure yourself.
snippet.textOriginal:
You don't pull your cutaway and then start looking for your reserve handle - when you cut away, your harness will shift and you'll loose precious time. You either have one hand on each handle, or you grab the cutaway, fix your eyes on the reserve handle, *then* you pull cutaway. All training every on earth will teach you one of these two procedures. 

And you should absolutely forget about the main potentially opening the reserve. It probably will, but your mindset should 100% be that you need to do the full procedure yourself.
